Ondo State governor, Rotimi Akeredolu has dissolved his cabinet.  The move was made ahead of the February 24 second term inauguration of the governor.  The announcement was made during the valedictory meeting of the State Executive Council meeting. While appreciating the members of the State Executive Council for their support for his administration in the last four years, Akeredolu lauded them for their dedication to duty. The governor said they had worked together as one and the interest of the state had remained paramount throughout their services to the state government.  Source By Ayodeji Alabi Akure - Gov. Oluwarotimi Akeredolu of Ondo State has relieved three of his commissioners of their duties and subsequently nominated five other people as commissioner designates. This was contained in a statement made available to newsmen in Akure on Tuesday by Mr Olusegun Ajiboye, the Chief Press… In "News" By Remi Bamgbose Okitipupa (Ondo State) -   Gov. Oluwarotimi Akeredolu of Ondo State on Tuesday promised to use every administrative process to reconnect the sothern part of the state, that had been in darkness for a decade, to the national grid. He made the promise while addressing stakeholders at… In "News" About two weeks before Ondo State Governor Rotimi Akeredolu tested positive for COVID-19, he attended a political event without wearing a mask or observing social distancing, and sneezed at least once, a video has shown. The footage, first published by Sahara Reporters, showed Mr Akeredolu surrounded by a crowd of… In "Politics"